I"Ð<h1 id="voron-v00---skr-mini-e3-v20-wiring">Voron V0.0 - SKR mini E3 V2.0 Wiring</h1>

<h2 id="mcu">MCU</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Plug in stepper motors for X, Y, Z, and E in positions Xm, Ym, ZAm, and Em</li>
  <li>Plug Hot End thermistor to thermistor TH0</li>
  <li>Plug Hot End heater in to E0</li>
  <li>Plug Hot End Fan in to FAN0</li>
  <li>Plug Part Cooling Fan in to HB</li>
  <li>Plug Bed Thermistor in to THB</li>
  <li>Connect SSR pins to PT-DET connector
    <ul>
      <li>Crydom SSR: SSR Input + =&gt; PC12, SSR Input =&gt; GND</li>
      <li>MagicStudios / Knacro 1-Channel SSR: CH1 =&gt; PC12, DC- =&gt; GND, DC+ =&gt; NC</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Connect X end stop to X-STOP connector</li>
  <li>Connect Y end stop to Y-STOP connector</li>
  <li>Connect Z end stop to Z-STOP connector</li>
  <li>Wire 24V and -V from DC power supply to VIN and GND</li>
  <li>Connect USB Cable to your SKR mini E3, but do not connect it yet to your Raspberry Pi</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="./images/v0-miniE3-v20-mcu.png" alt="" /></p>

<h3 id="wiring-for-magicstudios--knacro-1-channel-ssr">Wiring for MagicStudios / Knacro 1-Channel SSR</h3>

<p>The MagicStudios / Knacro SSR requires 3 wires instead of the 2 referenced above.</p>

